    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nOriginally reported by @yochem here: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/33707#issuecomment-2838424786.\n\nHere's one way to reproduce (my neovim is configured with `lua_ls`).\n\n1. Create `test.lua`:\n   ```lua\n   for _, client in ipairs(vim.lsp.get_clients()) do\n       lsp.buf_detach_client(0, client.id)\n   end\n   ```\n2. `vi test.lua`\n3. Verify that `:checkhealth lsp` shows a lsp. Note the one client attached to one buffer.\n   ```\n   vim.lsp: Active Clients ~\n   - lua_ls (id: 1)\n     - Version: 3.14.0\n     - Root directory: nil\n     - Command: { \"lua-language-server\" }\n     - Settings: vim.empty_dict()\n     - Attached buffers: 1\n   ```\n4. Run the current file as lua: `:source`\n5. Run `:checkhealth lsp` again. Note how there are no attached buffers for the `lua_ls` client:\n   ```\n   vim.lsp: Active Clients ~\n   - lua_ls (id: 1)\n     - Version: 3.14.0\n     - Root directory: nil\n     - Command: { \"lua-language-server\" }\n     - Settings: vim.empty_dict()\n     - Attached buffers: \n   ```\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`lsp.buf_detach_client` stops the corresponding LSP client + server when the client is no longer attached to any buffers.",
