            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> I think [@mfussenegger](https://github.com/mfussenegger) may have had comments on this awhile back, can't remember.\n\nYes - I'm opposed because for many languages starting up the server takes some time and closing the last buffer for a language doesn't mean you're done working.  And worse, you can run into races and corrupted state files if one process is still shutting down (and saving files on disk), while another is starting up if you close + re-open quickly.\n\nImho auto-close shouldn't be done without opt-in. And the opt-in can be done with some autocmd's without much boilerplate.\n\nSee also discussion in https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/14430",
