            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> See also discussion in https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/14430\n\nAh, useful, thanks! It does seem like it's worth revisiting the topic, because that issue was closed with a now obsolete [comment about neovim core not supporting heuristics to start language servers](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/14430#issuecomment-1848355381).\n\n> And worse, you can run into races and corrupted state files if one process is still shutting down (and saving files on disk), while another is starting up if you close + re-open quickly.\n\nInteresting! IMO, this race condition feels like a reason to put some logic into neovim core. Not auto-close, but some logic to ensure that we don't start a LSP when that very same LSP is still in the process of stopping. Once we've resolved that core issue, then I feel like we could revisit the topic of if it makes sense to auto-close LSPs immediately (or after some delay) once they're no longer attached to any buffers. What do you think, @mfussenegger?",
